---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const chromeStore =
  "https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/%E2%97%86-pitchlab-mk2-%E2%80%94-virtual/achkpjadifhgadgojjiinmcebegneajd";
---
<Base
  title="PitchLab MK2 · Virtual Deck Engine"
  description="Browser-based reference deck for DJs and diggers: coherent playback behaviour, live BPM analysis, filters and proper metering."
>
  <h1>PitchLab MK2 — Virtual Deck Engine</h1>

  <p class="muted">
    A browser-based reference deck for DJs and crate diggers.
    It’s built for listening and verification while previewing music online.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <p>
      No time-stretching. No key lock.
      The deck behaves like a playback system, not like a DAW.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      Designed for decisions, not performance.
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top:14px">
      <a
        class="btn"
        href={chromeStore}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Chrome Web Store
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What it is</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      PitchLab MK2 is an analysis + preview tool for selectors who want
      consistent playback behaviour when checking music on platforms like
      YouTube, Bandcamp and embedded previews.
    </p>

    <p class="muted">
      It is not a DJ app, not a DAW, and not a beatgrid tool.
      It’s a reference environment: change rate and you hear the real-world consequences.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Playback engine</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      The engine changes playback rate directly and avoids “helpful” correction layers.
      The goal is predictable behaviour, not convenience.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Direct rate control via <code>HTMLMediaElement.playbackRate</code></li>
      <li>Browser pitch-preserve flags explicitly disabled</li>
      <li>No phase vocoder / time-stretch layer</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>Live BPM analysis</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      PitchLab MK2 includes real-time BPM estimation derived from the signal
      (envelope extraction + autocorrelation). It does not rely on page metadata.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Real-time BPM estimation from the audio stream (when accessible)</li>
      <li>Confidence-scored output</li>
      <li>Half-time / double-time correction</li>
      <li>Stabilisation logic to reduce jitter</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="hr" style="margin:16px 0;"></div>

    <p><strong>Manual BPM tools</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Manual base BPM input</li>
      <li>Tap BPM with snapping and hysteresis</li>
      <li>Reset logic when playback context changes</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>Mixer & filters</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      PitchLab MK2 builds a local Web Audio graph on top of the page media.
      Nothing is uploaded, nothing leaves the browser.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Pre-analysis gain stage</li>
      <li>High-pass filter</li>
      <li>Low-pass filter</li>
      <li>Stereo-safe routing</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="hr" style="margin:16px 0;"></div>

    <p><strong>Typical uses</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Isolate rhythmic content for BPM verification</li>
      <li>Reduce vocals / noise while analysing</li>
      <li>Quick tonal balance checks during preview</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>Metering</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      Proper metering matters when you’re making decisions quickly.
      PitchLab MK2 provides stereo level measurement with realistic behaviour.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Dual-channel (L/R) analysis</li>
      <li>Peak dBFS + RMS-derived VU</li>
      <li>Hardware-inspired ballistics (attack / release)</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">
      Measurement, not decoration.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Embed aware</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      The extension is built to deal with modern web playback:
      multiple frames, embedded players and inconsistent page structure.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Works across iframes and embedded players</li>
      <li>Syncs state between frames when needed</li>
      <li>Targets the correct media element automatically</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>Design principles</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <ul>
      <li>No hidden correction</li>
      <li>No “DJ-friendly” compromises</li>
      <li>Predictable response across the entire range</li>
      <li>Built to behave like a deck, not like software</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>What it is not</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <ul>
      <li>❌ Time-stretching engine</li>
      <li>❌ Key-lock tool</li>
      <li>❌ Beat-gridding system</li>
      <li>❌ DJ performance app</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">
      Those already exist. This exists for people who want a clean reference.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Chrome Web Store blurb</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p class="muted">
      PitchLab MK2 is a browser-based reference deck for DJs and crate diggers.
      It provides coherent playback behaviour, real-time BPM analysis, filtering and proper metering
      while previewing music on platforms like YouTube and Bandcamp.
      No time-stretching. No key lock.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
